{
  "stem": "21437.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I felt such a sense of belonging.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I wanted to be friends with others too.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I liked them too.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But somehow without knowing me, without giving me a chance, I was Jewish but it was not just myself.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There were close to 500 children in this town.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And there was--",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--for as long-- close to 500 Jewish children.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "By the time, as for as long as I can remember, as long as my memory reaches back, Hitler was already in power.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You see?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then the burning of the books took place, and then the Nuremberg laws, you know.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "All of this as they identified-- I mean, I'm generalizing, I know.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But this is how it was to me.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I am speaking now about the perception of a child.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "To me, they seemed to be so strong and so powerful, and I-- where I walked, I always felt that I walk, that this was not my territory.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "That I was not really, you know, by the grace of God or whoever, that I walked those streets.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I mean, I-- I walked down those streets.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But this was not-- does not belong to me.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I was not welcome there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, for the first time when I came into Australia, I did not have to look over my shoulder.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But for as long as I remember, till then I always knew that I have to look in the back of me and in the front of me.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But again, a child adjust and adapts.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And this was the way-- this was our lifestyle.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And it was in the beginning very confusing because at home, that was this atmosphere that as children we were so cherished and so nurtured, and we felt so-- so important.",
      "word_count": 31
    }
  ],
